&lt;p&gt;THIS POST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All post holders will provide cover as general urologists for elective and emergency work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities will also include the supervision of junior staff, involvement in a regular teaching programme, participating in the weekly urology meetings (MDT/stone committee) and monthly departmental audit meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be expected to produce a number of basic science or clinical research papers within the time allotted for research during the week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will focus on the sub-specialist management of cancer patients and will be trained in open as well as laparoscopic renal and prostate surgery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
